This paper deals with game theory and its solution concepts, which are commonly studied in the computer science subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also uses knowledge-based programs, which are a type of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses logical reasoning and formal methods, which are topics in the subfield of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also touches on multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and decision-making (cs.DS), which are relevant to game theory.
